Opportunity

J.P. Morgan's Global Quantitative Research (QR) team provides a challenging work environment and excellent opportunities to learn and grow in the Firm's global network.

 The Credit Derivatives QR team is responsible for the pricing models for credit derivatives, for the development and calculations of investable indices for Credit and the risk management solutions used for these products. Our team works in close collaboration with the technology, structuring and trading and sales teams.

 The opportunity is to join our team and focus on the following projects:




 Implementation and development of the official calculation engine for Credit Investable Indices, risk-premia strategies, alpha, beta, flexible indices (client-driven), etc.;

 Development and support of the risk management platform used by traders to hedge indices traded with our clients;

 Develop and improve models for the pricing and risk management of credit derivatives;

 Work in very close partnership with the structuring and trading teams to develop business opportunities, drive innovation and participate in the development of JPMorgan branded systematic trading strategies;

 Contribute to the cross-asset development platform Athena with our technology partners;

 Collaborate with other quantitative research and control teams to support the trading desk.



 Requirements



 Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities;

 MS or PhD degree in a quantitative field: Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, Physics, Engineering (or equivalent);

 Experience working with quantitative models, ideally with exposure to Credit;

 Excellent communication skills to convey complex and technical concepts;

 Strong coding skills, preferably with some C++ and Python experience;

 Attention to details and focus on the quality of deliverables and code sustainability.

